+The auto-retry evaluation intentionally runs before dispatch-request
+processing. When all classifier, probe, retry-control, and safety guards pass,
+`AutoRetry::DecisionEngine` writes a request sequence whose first request is
+the same `hive markers clear` command a human would run and whose continuation
+is `hive run <slug> --stage <stage> --json`. The dispatcher can therefore
+observe and dispatch the marker clear in the same tick, while the same-stage
+rerun is promoted only after that clear exits 0. No special resume path exists.
+`daemon.auto_retry.enabled: false` disables this evaluation before any probes
+or request writes happen.
